          <span class="forum-in-reply-to"><a href="cost-living-vietnam-its-really-cheap.html#comment-168" class="active">(Reply to #62)</a></span>
    
        
    <span class="forum-post-number"><a href="cost-living-vietnam-its-really-cheap2679.html?page=1#comment-174" class="active">#112</a></span>
  </div> 
  <div class="forum-post-wrapper">
    <div class="forum-post-panel-sub">
              <div class="author-pane">tomo
</div>          </div>

    <div class="forum-post-panel-main clear-block">
      
      <div class="forum-post-content">
        <p>Since this blog is SAIGONist, I can't say so much definitively about Hanoi. ;)</p>
<p>You should be able to find a "room for rent", similar to a hotel room, with similar service like housekeeping, from $200/month and up.  Using that as a base, you can explore 'apartments', in small buildings.  More expensive would be serviced apartments for foreigners.</p>
      </div>

      
          </div>
  </div> 
