      <div class="forum-post-content">
        <p>You can assume that you can get everything I described that costs $600 in Saigon for less.  Food, labor, housing should all be cheaper in rural Vietnam than in the major cities.  I'm not sure how you can even spend $1600 US in Vietnam if you're living in the countryside as your entertainment options will be limited, and you won't be doing much expensive shopping.  You can consider buying a house for your budget for a year.</p>
