  <div class="forum-post-wrapper">
    <div class="forum-post-panel-sub">
              <div class="author-pane">tomo
</div>          </div>

    <div class="forum-post-panel-main clear-block">
      
      <div class="forum-post-content">
        <p>This is going to turn into a post on doing business in Vietnam soon.  </p>
<p>Bubble tea (Vietnamese tra sua tran chau) is quite popular in Vietnam with well-known chains such as Alo Tra and -18c.  There are also a lot of really simple stands selling it in their neighborhood, and these probably only take hundreds of dollars to set up.</p>
<p>Vietnamese food ingredients are cheap, international foods are more expensive.</p>
<p>Rent varies greatly depending on location. Alo Tra has tons of locations in cheap places. Other brands may choose to be located in very expensive prime locations inside the food courts of new department stores.</p>
<p>Bubble tea itself can cost from 7000 VND to 20000 or more.</p>
      </div>

      
