    <div class="forum-post-panel-main clear-block">
      
      <div class="forum-post-content">
        <p>True that. Thanks for leaving a comment David. </p>
<p>Many room-for-rent places in the backpacker area (especially on Co Giang and Co Bac) are $200/mo or less.</p>
<p>Cooking at home is cheap and healthy.  You can pay even less than supermarkets by going to local wet markets.</p>
<p>I bought a brand new Honda motorbike for around $800.  If you have a day job and it's far, you can consider taking the bus (cheaper than gas).</p>
<p>Going out to Western restaurants is more expensive with mains starting in the $2.50 to $5 range, and up to $10 for the more expensive places.</p>
      </div>

      
          </div>
