    <div class="forum-post-panel-main clear-block">
      
      <div class="forum-post-content">
        <p>My definition of safe: not dying, not going to the hospital, not bleeding.</p>
<p>Sorry to hear that somebody you know was threatened physically. &nbsp;In the United States, it most certainly would have been at gunpoint.</p>
<p>In fact, there is little gun-related crime here compared to both developing and developed countries. &nbsp;It's hard to get a gun. &nbsp;There aren't carjackers everywhere. &nbsp;No drive-bys. &nbsp;No sectarian / separatist terrorism incidents. &nbsp;No random bombings of embassies or world trade centers.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>If you seriously are afraid to go out at night and seriously had to hire a car and driver for it, then you are just a paranoid fool. &nbsp;</p>
<p>And if you really believe that there's anything near a 50% chance of your home getting broken into then you're either a liar or an idiot. &nbsp;Please stop with the hyperbole.</p>      </div>

      
